The paper deals with the complexity of the reachability problem in Petri nets, which is a fundamental problem in the theory of verification. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including formal languages (cs.FL), logic (cs.LO), process calculi (cs.PL), and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) used in the context of Petri nets. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
